{
  "texts": [
    "However, the information from brain scans cannot be fully represented in 2D image slices, and the spatial link between adjacent slices is lost.",
    "Slicebased techniques typically focus on the brain center while ignoring other regions.",
    "Some searches extract sections of 2D images using exclusive techniques.",
    "The axial or horizontal, frontal, medial, and coronal planes are some examples of standard projections used in neuroimaging studies.",
    "A slicebased iron buildup model (Ren et al., 2019) is used to develop novel therapies for long-term diseases like AD."
  ]
}